    "narrative": "The Austin Waves offense is positioned for a high-ceiling outing today, headlined by **Jackson Merrill**, whose 75.10 efficiency score makes him our primary play. **Jackson Merrill** benefits from a prime leadoff spot against Sean Burke, and his 87% stolen base success rate against a \"slow delivery\" pitcher aligns perfectly with our organizational emphasis on speed. **Kyle Tucker** follows closely with a 70.51 score; despite a minor park penalty, he projects for a massive day against Michael McGreevy, whose 4.48 xERA provides the right environment for **Kyle Tucker** to hunt for extra-base hits. **Drake Baldwin** also emerges as a surprise core contributor at 68.14, bolstered by a +14% park adjustment that helps elevate his value even against a neutral platoon matchup.\n\nWe are navigating a few tactical risks, most notably the \"Lineup Pending\" status for several starters including **Josh Jung** and **Andy Pages**. While **Andy Pages** is locked in with a 60.24 score due to the soft matchup against McGreevy, the optimizer remained cautious with **Gunnar Henderson**. Although **Gunnar Henderson** has a +2% bump for his high-efficiency base-stealing potential against a slow-working Ryan Weathers, his overall score is suppressed to 56.12 due to a -15% platoon penalty, making him a start that hinges more on his legs than his bat today. **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** remains a staple at 60.85, though we are wary of his -16% SP skill penalty against Prielipp; we need him to capitalize on his elite .388 xwOBA to overcome the tough matchup.\n\nThe most difficult bench decision involved **Coby Mayo**, who landed at 53.08\u2014within striking distance of **Liam Hicks** and **Nasim Nunez**. While **Coby Mayo** offers a platoon edge against Weathers, the optimizer preferred the positional efficiency of **Nasim Nunez** and the slightly better projected volume of **Liam Hicks**. **Nolan Schanuel** also drew consideration but was ultimately sidelined due to a difficult matchup against Nolan McLean, whose sub-3.00 xERA is the most daunting hurdle in our projected lineup. We will continue to monitor the status of **Luis Robert Jr.**, **Jordan Westburg**, **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.**, **Jorge Polanco**, and **Heliot Ramos** to ensure our bench depth remains ready should these early-season injury or performance trends shift.",
